      <strong>Family Background:</strong><br>
      Reed Hastings was born on October 8, 1960, in Boston, Massachusetts, USA, into a comfortable, upper-middle-class family.
His father was an attorney for the Department of Health, Education and Welfare, and his mother was a Boston debutante and homemaker, instilling social grace and discipline in the household.
Growing up, Reed enjoyed academic freedom, intellectual curiosity, and outdoor adventure, but the family maintained a modest, frugal lifestyle despite their social status.
The combination of access to quality education, parental encouragement, and exposure to diverse opportunities gave Reed the confidence to pursue innovative and unconventional career paths.
